Note:
SwiftUI to HIR Translator - Converts SwiftUI AST to Runa HIR

This file translates SwiftUI Abstract Syntax Trees into Runa's High-level
Intermediate Representation (HIR). This enables SwiftUI declarative UI code
to be processed as native Runa data structures and translated to other UI frameworks.

Translation Mapping:
- SWIFTUI_VIEW_STRUCT → Dictionary with:
  - "_type": "view_struct"
  - "name": struct name
  - "properties": List of property dictionaries
  - "body": View body dictionary
- SWIFTUI_VIEW_BODY → Dictionary with:
  - "_type": "view_body"
  - "view": View hierarchy dictionary
- SWIFTUI_VIEW_CONTAINER → Dictionary with:
  - "_type": "container"
  - "name": Container type (VStack, HStack, ZStack)
  - "parameters": Dictionary of parameters
  - "children": List of child views
  - "modifiers": List of modifiers
- SWIFTUI_VIEW_ELEMENT → Dictionary with:
  - "_type": "element"
  - "name": Element type (Text, Button, Image, etc.)
  - "parameters": Dictionary of parameters
  - "children": List of child views (for Button closures, etc.)
  - "modifiers": List of modifiers
- SWIFTUI_VIEW_MODIFIER → Dictionary with:
  - "_type": "modifier"
  - "name": Modifier name
  - "parameters": Dictionary of parameters
- SWIFTUI_PROPERTY → Dictionary with:
  - "_type": "property"
  - "name": Property name
  - "wrapper": Property wrapper name (@State, @Binding, etc.)
  - "type_annotation": Type annotation (optional)
  - "initial_value": Initial value expression (optional)
- SWIFTUI_CLOSURE → Dictionary with:
  - "_type": "closure"
  - "parameter": Parameter name (optional)
  - "body": List of statements
- SWIFTUI_EXPRESSION → Various HIR nodes (literals, identifiers, member access)
- SWIFTUI_LITERAL → HIR literal (string, number, boolean)
- SWIFTUI_IDENTIFIER → String literal

Features:
- Complete semantic preservation of SwiftUI structure
- Property wrapper metadata preservation
- View hierarchy preservation
- Modifier chain preservation
- State binding preservation
- Closure and expression translation
- Memory-safe translation

Dependencies:
- swiftui_parser.runa (for SwiftUI AST)
- compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa (for HIR nodes)
- compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/swiftui/swiftui_parser.runa" as Parser
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dict
Import "compiler/internal/string_utils.runa" as StringUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Translation Context
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Compact context for SwiftUI -> HIR translation: just the error channel
(sticky-error pattern) and position info that gets updated as the walk
descends. Position tracking lives on the context, not threaded through
arguments, so deeply-nested view hierarchies don't need to pass line/
column down every call.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
32-byte record (4 x i64): error_message at offset 0 (owned, allocated
copy), has_error at offset 8 (sticky flag), line at offset 16 and
column at offset 24 (updated by translate_swiftui_node_to_hir on every
node visit so error reporting cites the most recent node's coordinates).
@End Implementation

Type called "SwiftUIToHIRContext":
    error_message as Integer    Note: Error message (if any)
    has_error as Integer        Note: Boolean: 1 if error occurred
    line as Integer             Note: Current line number
    column as Integer           Note: Current column number
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Context Creation and Destruction
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Builds a fresh translation context with cleared error state. The
context is short-lived — one translation per SwiftUI AST input — so
no resource pooling is attempted; allocation cost is amortised across
the resulting HIR tree.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Single 32-byte allocation, OOM short-circuits to 0, all four slots
explicitly initialised to 0 (no fields are left uninitialised because
the destructor reads error_message to decide whether to free it).
@End Implementation

Process called "create_translation_context" returns Integer:
    Note: Create SwiftUI to HIR translation context

    Let context_size be 32  Note: SwiftUIToHIRContext: 4 fields × 8 bytes
    Let context be proc allocate from Layout with context_size

    If context is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Initialize context
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 0, 0   Note: error_message = null
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 8, 0   Note: has_error = false
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 16, 0  Note: line = 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 24, 0  Note: column = 0

    Return context
End Process

@Reasoning:
Releases the context plus any owned error message. The only owned
heap resource on the context is the error_message buffer; everything
else is integer/pointer-aliased. Null context returns success so
defensive double-destroy is safe.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads error_message at offset 0, frees it via Layout deallocate if
non-null, then deallocates the 32-byte context struct. Returns 1 on
all paths including null-context (already-destroyed contract).
@End Implementation

Process called "destroy_translation_context" takes context as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Destroy translation context

    If context is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Free error message if exists
    Let error_message be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0

    If error_message is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with error_message
    End If

    proc deallocate from Layout with context

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Error Handling
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Records the current error message while replacing any previous one.
Unlike most sticky-error implementations in this codebase, this one
overwrites instead of preserving the first error — useful for SwiftUI
where the last error is usually the most actionable (deep view-tree
issues mask shallow ones).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the existing error pointer from offset 0 and frees it if
non-null (avoids leaking the prior buffer). Then computes msg_length,
allocates msg_length+1 bytes, copies the message in via memory_copy,
NUL-terminates at offset msg_length, and stores the new pointer at
offset 0. Sets has_error to 1 at offset 8 (sticky thereafter — never
cleared even if a future call overwrites the message).
@End Implementation

Process called "set_translation_error" takes context as Integer, message as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set translation error message

    Let error_message be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0

    Note: Free previous error if exists
    If error_message is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with error_message
    End If

    Note: Copy error message
    Let msg_length be proc string_length from StringCore with message
    Let new_error be proc allocate from Layout with msg_length plus 1

    If new_error is not equal to 0:
        proc memory_copy from Layout with new_error, 0, message, 0, msg_length
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with new_error, msg_length, 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 0, new_error
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 8, 1  Note: has_error = true

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Public predicate for the sticky-error flag. Used by the top-level
translate_swiftui_to_hir to decide whether to discard the partial
HIR result.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Returns the int64 at context offset 8 directly. The flag is 0/1 so
the caller can treat the return value as a boolean.
@End Implementation

Process called "has_translation_error" takes context as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if translation has error

    Let has_error be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 8

    Return has_error
End Process

@Reasoning:
Public accessor that hands the caller the (owned-by-context) error
message pointer. Caller must not free it — the context's destructor
owns the lifetime.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Returns the pointer at offset 0. Returns 0 (null) if no error has
been set yet. Callers reading the buffer must treat it as
NUL-terminated since set_translation_error always writes a trailing 0.
@End Implementation

Process called "get_error_message" takes context as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get translation error message

    Let error_message be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0

    Return error_message
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SwiftUI Node to HIR Translation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Master dispatcher that routes SwiftUI AST nodes to their specialised
HIR translator based on the node-type tag at offset 0. Ten node kinds
are handled: view struct, view body, container (VStack/HStack/ZStack),
element (Text/Button/Image), modifier, property (with @State/@Binding/
etc wrappers), closure, expression, literal, identifier. Position info
on the context is updated on every visit so error reports cite the
current source location even after recursing.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null swiftui_node triggers a "Null SwiftUI node" error and returns 0.
Reads node_type at offset 0 plus line at offset 64 and column at
offset 72 (SwiftUI AST nodes are 80+ bytes — position lives near the
end). Writes line/column back to context offsets 16/24. Then runs a
linear sequence of If/Return on each of the 10 SWIFTUI_* tags from
the Parser module. Unknown tags hit the fallthrough which sets an
"Unknown SwiftUI node type" error and returns 0.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_swiftui_node_to_hir" takes context as Integer, swiftui_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate SwiftUI AST node to HIR node

    If swiftui_node is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "Null SwiftUI node"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get node type and position
    Let node_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 0
    Let line be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 64
    Let column be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 72

    Note: Update context position
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 16, line
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 24, column

    Note: Translate based on node type
    If node_type is equal to SWIFTUI_VIEW_STRUCT from Parser:
        Return proc translate_view_struct with context, swiftui_node
    End If

    If node_type is equal to SWIFTUI_VIEW_BODY from Parser:
        Return proc translate_view_body with context, swiftui_node
    End If

    If node_type is equal to SWIFTUI_VIEW_CONTAINER from Parser:
        Return proc translate_view_container with context, swiftui_node
    End If

    If node_type is equal to SWIFTUI_VIEW_ELEMENT from Parser:
        Return proc translate_view_element with context, swiftui_node
    End If

    If node_type is equal to SWIFTUI_VIEW_MODIFIER from Parser:
        Return proc translate_view_modifier with context, swiftui_node
    End If

    If node_type is equal to SWIFTUI_PROPERTY from Parser:
        Return proc translate_property with context, swiftui_node
    End If

    If node_type is equal to SWIFTUI_CLOSURE from Parser:
        Return proc translate_closure with context, swiftui_node
    End If

    If node_type is equal to SWIFTUI_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_expression with context, swiftui_node
    End If

    If node_type is equal to SWIFTUI_LITERAL from Parser:
        Return proc translate_literal with context, swiftui_node
    End If

    If node_type is equal to SWIFTUI_IDENTIFIER from Parser:
        Return proc translate_identifier with context, swiftui_node
    End If

    proc set_translation_error with context, "Unknown SwiftUI node type"
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: View Structure Translation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
A SwiftUI `struct MyView: View` is a top-level UI declaration. The HIR
representation flattens its name, its property list (each `@State var`
etc.), and its body (the var body { ... } block) into a single dict
tagged "view_struct". Children of the struct node are heterogeneous
(properties and one view-body) so a single pass over children performs
both jobs by inspecting child type tags.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads struct_name from offset 8 and children list from offset 48.
Creates a HIR dictionary, attaches "_type"="view_struct" and "name"
entries. Then iterates children in a single pass, dispatching:
SWIFTUI_PROPERTY -> translate_property and append to properties_list;
SWIFTUI_VIEW_BODY -> translate_view_body and remember as body_hir.
After the loop, adds "properties" (list) and conditionally "body"
(only if found) to the dict. The properties list is always added
even when empty so consumers can iterate without null checks.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_view_struct" takes context as Integer, swiftui_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate SwiftUI view struct to HIR dictionary

    Note: Get struct properties
    Let struct_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 8
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 48

    Note: Create HIR dictionary for struct
    Let hir_dict be proc create_hir_dictionary_literal from HIR

    If hir_dict is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "Failed to create HIR dictionary"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Add type metadata
    Let type_value be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with "view_struct"
    proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "_type", type_value

    Note: Add struct name
    Let name_value be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with struct_name
    proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "name", name_value

    Note: Translate properties and body
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let child_count be proc size from List with children

        If child_count is greater than 0:
            Let properties_list be proc create_hir_list_literal from HIR
            Let body_hir be 0
            Let child_index be 0

            While child_index is less than child_count:
                Let child_node be proc get_at from List with children, child_index
                Let child_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child_node, 0

                If child_type is equal to SWIFTUI_PROPERTY from Parser:
                    Let property_hir be proc translate_property with context, child_node

                    If property_hir is not equal to 0:
                        proc add_list_element from HIR with properties_list, property_hir
                    End If
                Otherwise If child_type is equal to SWIFTUI_VIEW_BODY from Parser:
                    Set body_hir to proc translate_view_body with context, child_node
                End If

                Set child_index to child_index plus 1
            End While

            Note: Add properties list
            proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "properties", properties_list

            Note: Add body
            If body_hir is not equal to 0:
                proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "body", body_hir
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Return hir_dict
End Process

@Reasoning:
The `var body: some View { ... }` of a SwiftUI struct typically wraps
a single root view (a container or element). The HIR shape is a tiny
dict tagged "view_body" with one "view" entry pointing at the root.
This intermediate wrapper exists so the downstream HIR consumer knows
where the actual UI tree starts versus the surrounding struct metadata.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads children at offset 48. Creates the HIR dict and tags it. If
there's at least one child, takes the first as the root view and
recursively translates it through translate_swiftui_node_to_hir, then
attaches as "view". Multiple-child bodies (which SwiftUI permits via
implicit Group wrapping) currently use only the first child — known
limitation, would need a Group wrapper in HIR if multi-root bodies
need preservation.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_view_body" takes context as Integer, swiftui_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate SwiftUI view body to HIR dictionary

    Note: Get children (view hierarchy)
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 48

    Note: Create HIR dictionary for body
    Let hir_dict be proc create_hir_dictionary_literal from HIR

    If hir_dict is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "Failed to create HIR dictionary"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Add type metadata
    Let type_value be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with "view_body"
    proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "_type", type_value

    Note: Translate view hierarchy
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let child_count be proc size from List with children

        If child_count is greater than 0:
            Note: Usually just one child (the root view)
            Let root_view be proc get_at from List with children, 0
            Let view_hir be proc translate_swiftui_node_to_hir with context, root_view

            If view_hir is not equal to 0:
                proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "view", view_hir
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Return hir_dict
End Process

@Reasoning:
Container views (VStack/HStack/ZStack/ScrollView/List/etc.) carry both
children (the stacked subviews) and parameters (alignment, spacing).
The HIR dict captures all four facets — name, parameters, children,
modifiers — so a renderer can reconstruct the layout call without
losing modifier order or parameter values.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads container_name (offset 8), modifiers (offset 40), children
(offset 48), parameters (offset 56). Creates the HIR dict and attaches
_type and name first. Parameters are translated via translate_parameters
if present. Children are iterated and each translated recursively
through the master dispatcher; only successful translations get added
(failed translations are dropped silently, the sticky-error flag
catches the failure for the top-level checker). Modifiers are iterated
similarly, using translate_view_modifier for each. Empty children or
modifier lists do not produce empty HIR entries — the keys are simply
absent when there's nothing to attach.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_view_container" takes context as Integer, swiftui_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate SwiftUI container view to HIR dictionary

    Note: Get container properties
    Let container_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 8
    Let modifiers be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 40
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 48
    Let parameters be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 56

    Note: Create HIR dictionary for container
    Let hir_dict be proc create_hir_dictionary_literal from HIR

    If hir_dict is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "Failed to create HIR dictionary"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Add type metadata
    Let type_value be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with "container"
    proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "_type", type_value

    Note: Add container name
    Let name_value be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with container_name
    proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "name", name_value

    Note: Translate parameters
    If parameters is not equal to 0:
        Let params_hir be proc translate_parameters with context, parameters

        If params_hir is not equal to 0:
            proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "parameters", params_hir
        End If
    End If

    Note: Translate children
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let child_count be proc size from List with children

        If child_count is greater than 0:
            Let children_hir be proc create_hir_list_literal from HIR
            Let child_index be 0

            While child_index is less than child_count:
                Let child_node be proc get_at from List with children, child_index
                Let child_hir be proc translate_swiftui_node_to_hir with context, child_node

                If child_hir is not equal to 0:
                    proc add_list_element from HIR with children_hir, child_hir
                End If

                Set child_index to child_index plus 1
            End While

            proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "children", children_hir
        End If
    End If

    Note: Translate modifiers
    If modifiers is not equal to 0:
        Let modifier_count be proc size from List with modifiers

        If modifier_count is greater than 0:
            Let modifiers_hir be proc create_hir_list_literal from HIR
            Let modifier_index be 0

            While modifier_index is less than modifier_count:
                Let modifier_node be proc get_at from List with modifiers, modifier_index
                Let modifier_hir be proc translate_view_modifier with context, modifier_node

                If modifier_hir is not equal to 0:
                    proc add_list_element from HIR with modifiers_hir, modifier_hir
                End If

                Set modifier_index to modifier_index plus 1
            End While

            proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "modifiers", modifiers_hir
        End If
    End If

    Return hir_dict
End Process

@Reasoning:
Leaf view elements (Text, Button, Image, TextField, Toggle, etc.)
have the same HIR shape as containers — name + parameters + children
+ modifiers — because some elements like Button still carry "children"
in the form of action closures or label views. Unifying the HIR shape
across containers and elements lets downstream renderers use a single
view-tree walk regardless of whether a node is structural or leaf.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Same field offsets as translate_view_container: name (8), modifiers
(40), children (48), parameters (56). HIR dict construction follows
the same pattern with _type set to "element" instead of "container".
Children handling supports closure children (Button labels, sheet
content) by recursing through the master dispatcher which can handle
SWIFTUI_CLOSURE nodes. Modifier list iteration is identical to
container translation.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_view_element" takes context as Integer, swiftui_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate SwiftUI element view to HIR dictionary

    Note: Get element properties
    Let element_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 8
    Let modifiers be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 40
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 48
    Let parameters be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 56

    Note: Create HIR dictionary for element
    Let hir_dict be proc create_hir_dictionary_literal from HIR

    If hir_dict is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "Failed to create HIR dictionary"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Add type metadata
    Let type_value be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with "element"
    proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "_type", type_value

    Note: Add element name
    Let name_value be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with element_name
    proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "name", name_value

    Note: Translate parameters
    If parameters is not equal to 0:
        Let params_hir be proc translate_parameters with context, parameters

        If params_hir is not equal to 0:
            proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "parameters", params_hir
        End If
    End If

    Note: Translate children (closures for Button, etc.)
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let child_count be proc size from List with children

        If child_count is greater than 0:
            Let children_hir be proc create_hir_list_literal from HIR
            Let child_index be 0

            While child_index is less than child_count:
                Let child_node be proc get_at from List with children, child_index
                Let child_hir be proc translate_swiftui_node_to_hir with context, child_node

                If child_hir is not equal to 0:
                    proc add_list_element from HIR with children_hir, child_hir
                End If

                Set child_index to child_index plus 1
            End While

            proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "children", children_hir
        End If
    End If

    Note: Translate modifiers
    If modifiers is not equal to 0:
        Let modifier_count be proc size from List with modifiers

        If modifier_count is greater than 0:
            Let modifiers_hir be proc create_hir_list_literal from HIR
            Let modifier_index be 0

            While modifier_index is less than modifier_count:
                Let modifier_node be proc get_at from List with modifiers, modifier_index
                Let modifier_hir be proc translate_view_modifier with context, modifier_node

                If modifier_hir is not equal to 0:
                    proc add_list_element from HIR with modifiers_hir, modifier_hir
                End If

                Set modifier_index to modifier_index plus 1
            End While

            proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "modifiers", modifiers_hir
        End If
    End If

    Return hir_dict
End Process

@Reasoning:
Modifiers (.padding(), .foregroundColor(), .background(), .frame())
are the most common SwiftUI extension point — they post-process a view
with parameters. The HIR shape is name + parameters (no children, no
nested modifiers — SwiftUI modifiers are flat at the AST level even
though they chain syntactically). Order matters and is preserved by
the containing view's "modifiers" list ordering.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads modifier_name from offset 8 and parameters from offset 56.
Builds the HIR dict with _type="modifier" and the name entry.
Parameters are translated through the shared translate_parameters
helper which understands both named and positional argument forms.
Modifiers without parameters (e.g., .padding() with default value)
simply omit the "parameters" key.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_view_modifier" takes context as Integer, swiftui_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate SwiftUI view modifier to HIR dictionary

    Note: Get modifier properties
    Let modifier_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 8
    Let parameters be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 56

    Note: Create HIR dictionary for modifier
    Let hir_dict be proc create_hir_dictionary_literal from HIR

    If hir_dict is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "Failed to create HIR dictionary"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Add type metadata
    Let type_value be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with "modifier"
    proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "_type", type_value

    Note: Add modifier name
    Let name_value be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with modifier_name
    proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "name", name_value

    Note: Translate parameters
    If parameters is not equal to 0:
        Let params_hir be proc translate_parameters with context, parameters

        If params_hir is not equal to 0:
            proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "parameters", params_hir
        End If
    End If

    Return hir_dict
End Process

@Reasoning:
Properties on a SwiftUI struct carry a property wrapper that drives
state behaviour: @State (owned local state), @Binding (borrowed state
from parent), @StateObject (owned ObservableObject), @ObservedObject
(borrowed ObservableObject), @EnvironmentObject (DI-injected), etc.
The wrapper name is the single most important piece of metadata to
preserve because downstream tooling routes state-binding logic based
on it.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads name (offset 8), wrapper (offset 24), type_annotation (offset 32),
children (offset 48, where the optional initial-value expression lives).
HIR dict gets _type="property" and the property name unconditionally.
Wrapper and type_annotation are added only when non-null (a property
might be a plain `var` without a wrapper, or untyped). The initial
value, if present, is the first child and gets translated recursively
through translate_swiftui_node_to_hir then attached as "initial_value".
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_property" takes context as Integer, swiftui_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate SwiftUI property to HIR dictionary

    Note: Get property properties
    Let property_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 8
    Let wrapper be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 24
    Let type_annotation be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 32
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 48

    Note: Create HIR dictionary for property
    Let hir_dict be proc create_hir_dictionary_literal from HIR

    If hir_dict is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "Failed to create HIR dictionary"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Add type metadata
    Let type_value be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with "property"
    proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "_type", type_value

    Note: Add property name
    Let name_value be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with property_name
    proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "name", name_value

    Note: Add wrapper name
    If wrapper is not equal to 0:
        Let wrapper_value be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with wrapper
        proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "wrapper", wrapper_value
    End If

    Note: Add type annotation
    If type_annotation is not equal to 0:
        Let type_value2 be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with type_annotation
        proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "type_annotation", type_value2
    End If

    Note: Translate initial value
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let child_count be proc size from List with children

        If child_count is greater than 0:
            Note: First child is initial value expression
            Let initial_value_node be proc get_at from List with children, 0
            Let initial_value_hir be proc translate_swiftui_node_to_hir with context, initial_value_node

            If initial_value_hir is not equal to 0:
                proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "initial_value", initial_value_hir
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Return hir_dict
End Process

@Reasoning:
SwiftUI closures appear in many places: Button actions ({ ... }),
ForEach iterations ({ item in ... }), .onAppear handlers, sheet
content builders, etc. The HIR captures the optional single parameter
name (Swift's `value in` form) and the body as an ordered list of
statements. Multiple statements survive as a list rather than a block
node because SwiftUI closure bodies are flat statement sequences.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads parameter_name (offset 8) and children (offset 48, where body
statements live). HIR dict gets _type="closure" and parameter (only
if parameter_name is non-null — many closures take no named parameter).
Iterates children, recursively translating each through the master
dispatcher, accumulating results into a HIR list named "body". The
list is only attached when at least one child translated successfully;
empty bodies are common with placeholder closures and don't merit
an empty list entry.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_closure" takes context as Integer, swiftui_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate SwiftUI closure to HIR dictionary

    Note: Get closure properties
    Let parameter_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 8
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 48

    Note: Create HIR dictionary for closure
    Let hir_dict be proc create_hir_dictionary_literal from HIR

    If hir_dict is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "Failed to create HIR dictionary"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Add type metadata
    Let type_value be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with "closure"
    proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "_type", type_value

    Note: Add parameter name
    If parameter_name is not equal to 0:
        Let param_value be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with parameter_name
        proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "parameter", param_value
    End If

    Note: Translate body statements
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let child_count be proc size from List with children

        If child_count is greater than 0:
            Let body_hir be proc create_hir_list_literal from HIR
            Let child_index be 0

            While child_index is less than child_count:
                Let child_node be proc get_at from List with children, child_index
                Let stmt_hir be proc translate_swiftui_node_to_hir with context, child_node

                If stmt_hir is not equal to 0:
                    proc add_list_element from HIR with body_hir, stmt_hir
                End If

                Set child_index to child_index plus 1
            End While

            proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "body", body_hir
        End If
    End If

    Return hir_dict
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Expression and Literal Translation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Four expression flavours are flattened here based on lexical inspection
of the value string: $-prefix => state binding, contains-`.` =>
member access, name+parameters => function call, else identifier.
Doing the classification here means the SwiftUI parser doesn't need
distinct AST tags for each — the lexical hints carry enough info.
The state-binding detection in particular relies entirely on the `$`
prefix because SwiftUI source uses `$state` syntax verbatim.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads expr_value (offset 16), expr_name (offset 8), parameters
(offset 56). Two-stage dispatch. Stage 1 (expr_value present): first
byte test for ASCII 36 ($) -> emit binding dict; otherwise scan for
ASCII 46 (.) via memory_get_byte loop and emit member_access dict if
found; else emit a bare string literal. Stage 2 (expr_value null
but expr_name with parameters present): emit a function_call dict
with name and translated parameters. Falls through to "Invalid
expression" error if neither stage matches.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_expression" takes context as Integer, swiftui_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate SwiftUI expression to HIR

    Note: Get expression value
    Let expr_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 16
    Let expr_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 8
    Let parameters be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 56

    Note: Check if this is a state binding ($variable)
    If expr_value is not equal to 0:
        Let first_char be proc memory_get_byte from Layout with expr_value, 0

        If first_char is equal to 36:  Note: ASCII for '$'
            Note: State binding
            Let hir_dict be proc create_hir_dictionary_literal from HIR

            If hir_dict is equal to 0:
                proc set_translation_error with context, "Failed to create HIR dictionary"
                Return 0
            End If

            Let type_value be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with "binding"
            proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "_type", type_value

            Let value_hir be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with expr_value
            proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "value", value_hir

            Return hir_dict
        End If

        Note: Check if this is member access (Type.member or .member)
        Let value_length be proc string_length from StringCore with expr_value
        Let has_dot be 0
        Let dot_index be 0

        While dot_index is less than value_length:
            Let char be proc memory_get_byte from Layout with expr_value, dot_index

            If char is equal to 46:  Note: ASCII for '.'
                Set has_dot to 1
                Break
            End If

            Set dot_index to dot_index plus 1
        End While

        If has_dot is equal to 1:
            Note: Member access
            Set hir_dict to proc create_hir_dictionary_literal from HIR

            If hir_dict is equal to 0:
                proc set_translation_error with context, "Failed to create HIR dictionary"
                Return 0
            End If

            Set type_value to proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with "member_access"
            proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "_type", type_value

            Set value_hir to proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with expr_value
            proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "value", value_hir

            Return hir_dict
        End If

        Note: Simple value expression
        Return proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with expr_value
    End If

    Note: Check if this is a function call (has name and parameters)
    If expr_name is not equal to 0:
        If parameters is not equal to 0:
            Note: Function call
            Set hir_dict to proc create_hir_dictionary_literal from HIR

            If hir_dict is equal to 0:
                proc set_translation_error with context, "Failed to create HIR dictionary"
                Return 0
            End If

            Set type_value to proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with "function_call"
            proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "_type", type_value

            Let name_value be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with expr_name
            proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "name", name_value

            Let params_hir be proc translate_parameters with context, parameters

            If params_hir is not equal to 0:
                proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, "parameters", params_hir
            End If

            Return hir_dict
        End If
    End If

    proc set_translation_error with context, "Invalid expression"
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
SwiftUI literals arrive from the parser as strings without type tags.
This routine recovers the typed HIR literal by inspecting the string
shape: "true"/"false" -> bool, all-digit (with optional dot/minus)
-> int/float, anything else -> string. Recovering the type lets the
HIR carry strongly-typed literal nodes which the optimiser and
renderer can use without parsing again.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads literal_value at offset 16. Null triggers error+0. Three-pass
classification: (1) strings_equal against "true" and "false" routes
to create_hir_boolean_literal; (2) iterate the bytes, every char must
be ASCII 48-57 (digit), 46 (.), or 45 (-) — if all pass, route based
on whether a dot appeared (string_to_float -> float literal, else
string_to_int -> integer literal); (3) fall through to
create_hir_string_literal for the raw value. The numeric scanner is
permissive — it accepts `-` anywhere, not just leading — but the
downstream string_to_int/float will reject malformed forms.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_literal" takes context as Integer, swiftui_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate SwiftUI literal to HIR literal

    Note: Get literal value
    Let literal_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 16

    If literal_value is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "Null literal value"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check if it's a boolean
    Let is_true be proc string_equals from StringCore with literal_value, "true"
    Let is_false be proc string_equals from StringCore with literal_value, "false"

    If is_true is equal to 1:
        Return proc create_hir_boolean_literal from HIR with 1
    End If

    If is_false is equal to 1:
        Return proc create_hir_boolean_literal from HIR with 0
    End If

    Note: Check if it's a number (contains only digits, dot, minus)
    Let value_length be proc string_length from StringCore with literal_value
    Let is_number be 1
    Let has_dot be 0
    Let index be 0

    While index is less than value_length:
        Let char be proc memory_get_byte from Layout with literal_value, index

        Note: Check if character is digit (48-57), dot (46), or - (45)
        Let is_digit be 0

        If char is greater than or equal to 48:
            If char is less than or equal to 57:
                Set is_digit to 1
            End If
        End If

        If char is equal to 46:  Note: Dot
            Set is_digit to 1
            Set has_dot to 1
        End If

        If char is equal to 45:  Note: Minus
            Set is_digit to 1
        End If

        If is_digit is equal to 0:
            Set is_number to 0
            Break
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    If is_number is equal to 1:
        If has_dot is equal to 1:
            Note: Float literal
            Let float_value be proc string_to_float from StringUtils with literal_value
            Return proc create_hir_float_literal from HIR with float_value
        Otherwise:
            Note: Integer literal
            Let int_value be proc string_to_integer from StringUtils with literal_value
            Return proc create_hir_integer_literal from HIR with int_value
        End If
    End If

    Note: Otherwise it's a string literal
    Return proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with literal_value
End Process

@Reasoning:
Bare identifiers (variable references, view names) become HIR string
literals — there's no separate "identifier" HIR node because the
identifier-vs-string distinction is recovered later from context
(an identifier appearing in a parameter slot is a name reference;
in a content slot it's display text).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads identifier_name from offset 8. Null triggers a "Null identifier
name" error and returns 0. Otherwise creates a HIR string literal
via create_hir_string_literal, which itself may fail (returns 0)
under OOM — in that case sets a "Failed to create HIR string literal"
error and returns 0.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_identifier" takes context as Integer, swiftui_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate SwiftUI identifier to HIR string literal

    Note: Get identifier name
    Let identifier_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with swiftui_node, 8

    If identifier_name is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "Null identifier name"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create HIR string literal for identifier
    Let hir_string be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with identifier_name

    If hir_string is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "Failed to create HIR string literal"
        Return 0
    End If

    Return hir_string
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Parameter Translation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
SwiftUI parameters live as a Dict keyed by either parameter name
(for named args like `alignment: .center`) or string-form integer
indices (for positional args). Preserving both forms uniformly as
Dict keys lets the HIR consumer treat them homogeneously — the
shape is "any string -> expression" without needing two paths.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null parameters_dict returns 0 (no parameters to translate). Otherwise
creates a HIR dict, gets the parameter keys via `keys from Dict`,
iterates the key list, fetches each value via `get from Dict`, and
recursively translates it through the master dispatcher. Successful
translations are attached to the HIR dict under the same key. Empty
key list returns the empty HIR dict.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_parameters" takes context as Integer, parameters_dict as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate SwiftUI parameters dictionary to HIR dictionary

    If parameters_dict is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create HIR dictionary for parameters
    Let hir_dict be proc create_hir_dictionary_literal from HIR

    If hir_dict is equal to 0:
        proc set_translation_error with context, "Failed to create HIR dictionary"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get parameter keys
    Let param_keys be proc keys from Dict with parameters_dict

    If param_keys is equal to 0:
        Return hir_dict
    End If

    Let key_count be proc size from List with param_keys
    Let key_index be 0

    While key_index is less than key_count:
        Let param_key be proc get_at from List with param_keys, key_index
        Let param_value be proc get from Dict with parameters_dict, param_key

        Note: Translate parameter value
        Let value_hir be proc translate_swiftui_node_to_hir with context, param_value

        If value_hir is not equal to 0:
            proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_dict, param_key, value_hir
        End If

        Set key_index to key_index plus 1
    End While

    Return hir_dict
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Top-Level Translation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Public top-level entry point. Manages the context lifetime so callers
just pass a SwiftUI AST and get a HIR dict (or 0 on error). The
context is created, used, and destroyed in this routine — callers
never see it. This isolation keeps the SwiftUI frontend's internal
state invisible to the rest of the driver.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Three-step sequence: create_translation_context (returns 0 on OOM),
translate_swiftui_node_to_hir on the root AST, then check
has_translation_error. On error, destroys the context and returns 0,
discarding the partial HIR result. On success, still destroys the
context (otherwise it leaks) and returns the HIR result. Note the
HIR result is independent of the context's lifetime — it's a separate
allocation chain owned by the HIR module.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_swiftui_to_hir" takes swiftui_ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate SwiftUI AST to HIR (top-level entry point)

    Note: Create translation context
    Let context be proc create_translation_context

    If context is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Translate SwiftUI AST to HIR
    Let hir_result be proc translate_swiftui_node_to_hir with context, swiftui_ast

    Note: Check for errors
    Let has_error be proc has_translation_error with context

    If has_error is equal to 1:
        proc destroy_translation_context with context
        Return 0
    End If

    proc destroy_translation_context with context

    Return hir_result
End Process
